name: Might Go actually be OOP? featuring Ronna Steinberg (Go Time #238)
summary: A conversation with Ronna Steinberg, who was an OOP developer for many years, and now is a Go Google Developer Expert. Ronna has been thinking about Go and OOP for awhile, asking herself whether or not Go is an object oriented programming language.
